:::summary
Western history is the story of the civilizations that grew from ancient Greece and Rome, passed through the crucible of Christian Europe, and produced the modern world. It is a story of ideas — democracy, philosophy, monotheism, science, and individual rights — that have shaped every nation on earth. For Latter-day Saints, Western history is also the providential stage on which the Restoration of the gospel took place.
